# Pipeline stages

The Beanstalk compiler is organised as a linear frontend pipeline followed by a builder-owned backend handoff. Each stage receives a deliberately narrowed input from the previous one, transforms it and passes a cleaner shape to the next.

## Category contract

- Stages 0-3 prepare and order source declarations.
- Stages 4-6 perform semantic resolution, HIR lowering and borrow validation.
- Stage 7 hands compiled modules to project builders and backend lowerers.

